Command,Description
pwd,Print Working Directory
cd foldername,Change directory
cd ..,Go back one directory
cd -,Go back to the previous working directory
cd ~ or cd,Go to the user's home directory
cd /,Go to the root directory
touch file,Create a single empty file
touch f1 f2,Create multiple files
touch file{1..5},Create 5 files (file1 to file5)
mkdir folder,Create a single directory
mkdir -p a/b/c,Create nested parent directories
